parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Delayed or Unavailable Recall Parts for Airbag Repair
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unavailability of recall parts for airbag repairs can leave vehicles without critical safety features, increasing the risk of injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: Receipt of recall notification
inability to schedule repair due to part unavailability
delayed or failed delivery of recall parts
lack of communication from dealership or manufacturer regarding part availability.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear ceiling lining can cause debris to fall from the ceiling, creating a distraction for the driver and potentially obstructing their view, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: The lining begins to fall from the rear ceiling of the vehicle
the glue that holds the lining in place wears out
debris falls from the ceiling.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the adhesive that holds the rear ceiling lining in place can cause the lining to detach, creating a distraction for the driver and potentially obstructing their view, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: The glue that holds the lining in place wears out
the lining begins to fall from the rear ceiling of the vehicle
debris falls from the ceiling.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Premature clutch failure can cause the clutch to malfunction, leading to difficulty shifting gears, and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch fails prematurely
the clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent loss of power while driving can cause the vehicle to stall or slow down unexpectedly, increasing the risk of accidents, especially on highways or busy roads.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly loses power
the accelerator pedal has no effect or minimal effect on the vehicle's speed
the vehicle barely moves despite pressing the accelerator pedal to the floor.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Premature warping of the front brake rotors can cause vibrations, uneven braking, and reduced stopping power, which can increase the risk of accidents and compromise vehicle safety.
symptoms: Vibrations or pulsations when applying the brakes
uneven braking
squealing or grinding noises when braking
excessive brake dust
and reduced stopping power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure to properly diagnose and address the underlying cause of premature brake rotor warping can lead to repeated failures, increased repair costs, and continued safety risks.
symptoms: Repeated brake rotor replacements
persistent brake-related issues despite repairs
and continued vibrations or uneven braking.
